# ============================================================================
#  HINOSO — Waitlist storage
#  Fill in ONE provider below, then: copy this file to `.env.local` and restart
#  the dev server (npm run dev). Signups flow into that provider's contact list,
#  where you can store them and send marketing emails.
#  (Leave everything blank and signups save to a local file — dev only.)
# ============================================================================


# ===========================  FREE OPTIONS  =================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Sender.net  —  FREE: ~2,500 subscribers + ~15,000 emails/month, no daily cap
#                 (highest free send volume — best if you want big blasts)  ⭐
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  1. Sign up free at sender.net (no card).
#  2. API key:  Settings → API access → create a token.
#  3. Group ID (optional):  Audience → Groups → open your group → ID in the URL.
#
# SENDER_API_KEY=your_token_here
# SENDER_GROUP_ID=optional_group_id


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  MailerLite  —  FREE: ~1,000 subscribers + ~12,000 emails/month, no daily cap
#                 (includes real marketing campaigns & automations)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  1. Sign up free at mailerlite.com (no card).
#  2. API key:   Integrations → API → "Generate new token".
#  3. Group ID (optional, to file signups in a "Waitlist" group):
#                Subscribers → Groups → open your group → the ID is in the URL.
#
# MAILERLITE_API_KEY=your_token_here
# MAILERLITE_GROUP_ID=optional_group_id


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Brevo  —  FREE: unlimited contacts + ~300 emails/day
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  1. Sign up free at brevo.com.
#  2. API key:  Settings → SMTP & API → API Keys → "Generate a new API key".
#  3. List ID (optional):  Contacts → Lists → your list → the numeric ID.
#
# BREVO_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# BREVO_LIST_ID=2


# =========================  OTHER PROVIDERS  ================================

# ---- Mailchimp  (free up to ~500 contacts) --------------------------------
#  Audience ID: Audience → Settings → "Audience name and defaults".
#  API key:     Account → Extras → API keys (ends with a datacenter, e.g. -us21).
# MAILCHIMP_API_KEY=your_api_key_here-us21
# MAILCHIMP_AUDIENCE_ID=your_audience_id_here

# ---- ConvertKit / Kit  (free up to ~10,000 subscribers) -------------------
#  API key: Settings → Advanced → API.   Form ID: the number in the form's URL.
# CONVERTKIT_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# CONVERTKIT_FORM_ID=1234567
